INTERSHOP IOM 4.5.0-SNAPSHOT Database Model   (revision 2ef001a0e1bd5ee0cf592fbf8236afcbbc122401)

Table oms.ShopDO

List of all shops and their basic configuration.

Columns 

References[1] Column Type Constraints[2] Default Comment
id bigint PK, UNIQUE, NOT_NULL  
active boolean Whether the shop is active or not.
If FALSE, no orders will be accepted and no product import will be processed.
If FALSE, messages e.g. responses, dispatches, return still will be accepted. 
availabilityTolerance integer Allowed delivery date deviation in days before using manual supplier assignment. Example 2. 
isB2B boolean NOT_NULL Whether the business model of the shop is B2B or not (B2C). 
CountryDefDO countryDefRef integer The country where the shop is located at. 
mapArticleId boolean NOT_NULL Whether an article Id of a new order are shop-specific and should be mapped to article Id of IOM. 
modificationDate timestamp without time zone  
name varchar(50) The name of the shop. 
OrderOptimizeDefDO orderOptimizeDefRef integer NOT_NULL The order optimization rule used by the shop. 
overwriteSelectedSupplierAllowed boolean Whether the supplier selection process (DOSE) can replace the selected supplier from shop.
The property references to order positions if the supplier is not able to deliver. Also see "preferredSupplierOnly". 
ShopDO parentRef bigint The parent shop instance. 
returnDeadline integer Deadline for returning articles in days. Example 30 
shopName varchar(50) UNIQUE The name of the shop as used by the shop. 
shopOrderSequenceName varchar(255) The name of the sequencer that should be used at order creation to generate shop-specific order numbers if not set by the shop. 
singleArticleInfo boolean NOT_NULL true Deprecated 
ShopOrderValidationDO shopOrderValidationRef bigint The validation rules that should be processed for a new order. 
hasSupplierPrefix boolean NOT_NULL Whether the shop uses a supplier prefix, e.g. article number has supplier Id as prefix. 
internalShopName varchar(50) UNIQUE, NOT_NULL The name of the shop as used by the IOM. Spaces are not allowed; lower case recommended. 
shopCustomerSequenceName varchar(255) The name of the sequencer that should be used at order creation to generate shop-specific customer numbers if not set by the shop. 
preferredSupplierOnly boolean Whether the DOSE-process can also use non-preferred suppliers if preferred suppliers are not able to deliver. Also see "overwriteSelectedSupplierAllowed". 
orderProcessingDelay varchar(50) Duration an order is in wait-state after creation before processing.
The cron expression can be used to either define the earliest time or a period of time as a delay after the order has been created. 
shopOrderSequenceNumberFormatString varchar(20) Pattern used to format the generated shop-specific order number of "shopOrderSequenceName". 
orderTokenValidityDuration varchar(50) Validity of an order token. Pattern: Year (y), Month (M), Day (d), Hour (h), Minute (m), Second (s) example: 7d4h30s 
SalesPriceCalculatorBeanDefDO salesPriceCalculatorBeanDefRef integer The custom implementation that should be used for sales price calculation instead of the default ones. 
amountDaysForPaymentReminderMailOfPrepaidOrders smallint Duration in days before a payment reminder e-mail will be send to a customer in case of missing payments. Example 30 
amountDaysForAutoCancellationOfPrepaidOrders smallint Duration in days before an auto-cancellation will be done in case of missing payments. Example 40 
isReservationWithDOSE boolean false Defines if the reservation service is using the DOSE process to evaluate the supplier 
shopRMANumberSequenceName varchar(255) The name of the database sequence that should be used to generate shop-specific RMA numbers. 
shopRMANumberSequenceFormatString varchar(20) Pattern used to format the generated shop-specific RMA number of "shopRMANumberSequenceName". Example RMA#{0} 
shippingCountryTaxMapping boolean NOT_NULL false Used to determine a fallback geolocation for the taxes when none is provided within an incoming order:

When false:
use ShopDO.country

When true:
- for all taxes located within a shippling bucket: use the country of the shipping bucket delivery address.
- for all taxes located outside a shippling bucket, e.g. in order charges: use the country of the first shipping bucket delivery address.
The last case is an arbitrary choice, and customers with shipping buckets to different countries should in fact always include the location as tax attribute.
